# Keep the Docker build context small and reproducible. Node/Go build outputs
# and local artifacts must never be copied into image builds — the Dockerfiles
# install/build them cleanly inside their own stages.
ui/node_modules
# ui/dist is intentionally NOT ignored: Dockerfile.wardynd's UI_STAGE=ui-prebuilt
# stage COPYs a host-built ui/dist for corp mirrors that can't fetch pnpm. The
# default UI_STAGE=ui-build stage rebuilds /ui/dist from source anyway (its own
# `pnpm build` overwrites whatever was copied), so including it is harmless there;
# the prebuilt stage guards against a stale bundle with a test -f index.html check.
**/node_modules
.git
bin/
dist/
data/
test/e2e/fixtures/**/*.cast
*.log
# Compiled binaries that may sit at the repo root from local `go build`.
/wardynd
/wardyn
/wardyn-proxy
/wardyn-rec
/wardyn-runner
# Secrets / local env files — NEVER copy into a build context (H4). deploy/compose/.env
# holds the WARDYN_AGE_KEY secret-store MASTER key; a repo-root `COPY . .` (Dockerfile.wardynd,
# Dockerfile.proxy, tetragon-ingest, the agent images) would otherwise layer it into builder
# images/cache. The compose stack passes .env at RUNTIME (env_file), never at build.
.env
**/.env
